    <string name="settings_ai_local_setup_full">Start the llama.cpp server with a command like:\n\n./llama-server -m /path/to/model.gguf --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080\n\nThe --host 0.0.0.0 parameter allows connections from other devices.\n\nThen find the IP address of the machine running the server. On Linux/macOS use ip a or ifconfig, on Windows use ipconfig. You need a local IPv4 address like 192.168.x.x or 10.x.x.x.\n\nYour phone must be on the same local network (the same Wi-Fi or LAN). In the app, enter the address in the format http://IP:port, for example http://192.168.1.15:8080.</string>
    <string name="settings_ai_setup_title">How to use it</string>
    <string name="settings_ai_setup_step_1">Run llama.cpp server on a computer in your local network or locally on Android via Termux.</string>
    <string name="settings_ai_setup_step_2">Enter IP:port or a full URL. For example: http://192.168.0.15:8080.</string>
    <string name="settings_ai_setup_step_3">If the server runs on another device, do not use localhost or 127.0.0.1.</string>
    <string name="settings_ai_setup_step_4">For llama.cpp, http:// is usually the correct option. https:// works only if the server is explicitly configured for TLS.</string>
